12:13.297 --> 12:15.386
you need to stop
suggesting that.

12:15.430 --> 12:17.867
Okay, yeah, yeah,
to-totally, yeah.

12:19.695 --> 12:22.916
Knock, knock, Joanie.

12:22.959 --> 12:25.048
Miss Nadja, is it really you?

12:25.092 --> 12:26.963
Yes, of course it is me.

12:27.007 --> 12:29.009
I was lying down there.

12:29.052 --> 12:32.360
Oh, I've missed you so much,
my little Joanie!

12:32.403 --> 12:35.406
So, did you have a good life?

12:35.450 --> 12:37.147
Uh, yes.

12:37.191 --> 12:39.497
I-I think so. Oh!

12:39.541 --> 12:41.935
I took a trip to Nova Scotia
at one point.

12:44.502 --> 12:47.462
And did you marry
that boy you liked?

12:47.505 --> 12:48.985
-Franklin?
-Yeah.

12:49.029 --> 12:51.031
Oh, yes, I...

12:51.074 --> 12:52.728
Oh, wow, look.

12:52.772 --> 12:55.949
You were very beautiful
for a very brief moment.

12:55.992 --> 12:56.950
Wait.

12:56.993 --> 12:59.256
Where did you get this necklace?

12:59.300 --> 13:01.041
This is my necklace.

13:01.084 --> 13:03.739
-Pardon?
-The jade one in this photo.

13:03.783 --> 13:07.395
You motherfucker!

13:07.438 --> 13:09.223
It was my prized jade necklace.

13:09.266 --> 13:11.225
It was given to me  by my mother when I was young,

13:11.268 --> 13:14.010
just before she was
eaten by a bear.

13:14.054 --> 13:15.664
I should have known
you would have stolen it!

13:15.707 --> 13:17.971
You were always
a sneaky little human shit!

13:18.014 --> 13:21.322
You know, if you listen to it,you can still hear her screams.

13:21.365 --> 13:23.280
-It was the type of jade

13:23.324 --> 13:24.891
that absorbs human screams.

13:24.934 --> 13:26.893
And she was really screaming.

13:26.936 --> 13:29.896
So it took it very strongly.
Thieving bitch!

13:29.939 --> 13:31.636
Give it back to me!

13:31.680 --> 13:33.203
You little brat, where is it?!

13:33.247 --> 13:34.639
I don't know what you're
talking about!

13:34.683 --> 13:35.989
You are a lying piece
of old cabbage!

13:36.032 --> 13:39.079
But I don't know what
you're talking-- help!

13:39.122 --> 13:41.908
Help! I'm having
an episode! Help!

13:41.951 --> 13:43.910
-She attacked me!
-Oh, no, she didn't.

13:43.953 --> 13:45.912
-Oh, she-she did.
-Nadia, go.

13:45.955 --> 13:47.739
Go enjoy yourself,
we'll take care of her.

13:47.783 --> 13:49.480
-Ma, she didn't attack you.
-She-she did.

13:49.524 --> 13:51.918
Mama? Mama?

13:51.961 --> 13:53.528
Scream for me.

13:56.357 --> 13:58.011
My mother gave it to me.

13:58.054 --> 14:00.927
She said, um, "I can't
wait to see you wear this

14:00.970 --> 14:04.104
for the rest of your life
every minute of every day."

14:04.147 --> 14:05.975
And then, honestly,
the next day,

14:06.019 --> 14:07.672
walked out the house
and bam-- bear.

14:07.716 --> 14:10.371
Mama, scream for me
if you're here.

14:10.414 --> 14:13.113
That is worse than a bible--
that burns my eyes.

14:15.158 --> 14:17.378
Mama?

14:19.423 --> 14:20.947
Mama!

14:23.645 --> 14:27.301
COLIN:
Sure, the guys on the field
are having a good time today,

14:27.344 --> 14:30.086
but they're not gonna be havingsuch a good time in 20 years.

14:30.130 --> 14:31.914
That's when they'll have

14:31.958 --> 14:34.525
applesauce sloshing
around in their skulls.

14:34.569 --> 14:37.833
Has anyone heard the ancient
screams of a very large woman?

14:37.877 --> 14:39.139
ANNOUNCER:
What a throw by...

14:39.182 --> 14:41.837
-The halftime show--

14:41.881 --> 14:43.795
a lot of people consider that
to be the highlight.

14:43.839 --> 14:45.493
I like the commercials.

14:45.536 --> 14:48.148
I like to see what they come
up with for the Clydesdales

14:48.191 --> 14:50.933
-each year.
-All right, bros, who's ready

14:50.977 --> 14:54.632
for piping-hot nachos
fresh from the microwave?

14:54.676 --> 14:57.505
FRANK:
Uh, Sean, those are batteries.

14:57.548 --> 14:59.986
LASZLO:
It is possible
to over-hypnotize,

15:00.029 --> 15:02.162
and I fear

15:02.205 --> 15:03.946
that's what we've done
with Sean.

15:03.990 --> 15:06.340
You see, there's various
levels of over-hypnosis.

15:06.383 --> 15:08.995
If it's not too serious, it's
what's called "Weak Brain."

15:09.038 --> 15:12.389
If it's slightly worrying, it's  called "Thoughtless Sallies."

15:12.433 --> 15:15.088
And if it's a fucking nightmare  and you can forget about him,

15:15.131 --> 15:16.393
it's "Brain Scramblies."

15:16.437 --> 15:17.742
Yes! Yes!

15:21.050 --> 15:23.357
Go, go, yeah,
no, oh, come on!

15:23.400 --> 15:26.012
How is that a yellow card?!
Are you kidding me?!

15:31.495 --> 15:34.542
Typically, when a vampire turnsa human's brain into pudding

15:34.585 --> 15:36.109
from over-hypnosis,

15:36.152 --> 15:38.241
the proper etiquette is

15:38.285 --> 15:40.200
to put them
out of their misery...

15:40.243 --> 15:42.071
by murdering them.

15:43.072 --> 15:44.552
We're not gonna kill him.

15:44.595 --> 15:46.989
It goes against
our non-killing agreement.

15:47.033 --> 15:49.252
Yes, but it is now
necessary to do

15:49.296 --> 15:51.254
the humane thing
and rip Sean's head off.

15:51.298 --> 15:53.691
-Uh, not now.

15:53.735 --> 15:55.171
We are taking
a human shit together.

15:55.215 --> 15:58.044
-Uh...
-Have either of you two seen

15:58.087 --> 16:00.046
a jade necklace containing
the bloodcurdling screams

16:00.089 --> 16:01.830
of my dead mother in here?

16:01.873 --> 16:03.614
Eh... oh, maybe check behind

16:03.658 --> 16:06.226
the Andy Garcia cross-stitch.

16:06.269 --> 16:08.271
SEAN:
No soap? Radio?

16:08.315 --> 16:10.491
Ha, bowling ball.

16:10.534 --> 16:13.276
Nandor wants to kill Sean 'causehe's got the Brain Scramblies.

16:13.320 --> 16:14.843
Well, then Nandor is correct.

16:14.886 --> 16:17.063
Have you gone soft,
my sweet syrup pie?

16:17.106 --> 16:18.716
No, my sweet syrup pie,
I've gone hard.

16:18.760 --> 16:20.718
-'Cause he's my best friend,
he's my pal.

16:20.762 --> 16:23.025
He's my homeboy,
my rotten soldier.

16:23.069 --> 16:25.375
He's my sweet cheese,
my good-time boy.

16:25.419 --> 16:27.638
Laszlo, this is clearly
what must be done.

16:29.989 --> 16:31.729
Oh, Yahtzee!

16:31.773 --> 16:33.427
For Sean's own sake.

16:33.470 --> 16:35.081
I'll go get
my head-ripping gloves.

16:35.124 --> 16:37.039
No, no, no, hang on, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

16:37.083 --> 16:38.432
We're not animals.

16:38.475 --> 16:40.738
Let's give him one
last night to remember.

16:40.782 --> 16:42.914
One magical night
on Earth before we...

16:42.958 --> 16:44.264
"whack" him.

16:44.307 --> 16:46.918
Well, okay, yes, that is fair.

16:48.311 --> 16:49.486
I can feel it, guys.

16:49.530 --> 16:51.706
I mean, I really think
we are, like,

16:51.749 --> 16:53.621
this close to finding
our first vampire.

16:53.664 --> 16:56.276
-Yes.
-Wait, so you guys

16:56.319 --> 16:58.278
have never actually...

16:58.321 --> 17:00.236
met or seen a real vampire.

17:00.280 --> 17:02.282
Well, come on,
it's not like they're just

17:02.325 --> 17:03.979
walking around
in broad daylight, you know?

17:04.023 --> 17:05.067
-Yeah.
-Throwing a football
in the park.

17:05.111 --> 17:06.634
-Seriously.
-Running errands.

17:06.677 --> 17:08.288
-Yeah.
-Going to the bank.

17:08.331 --> 17:10.116
-Eating a pretzel.
-Yeah.

17:10.159 --> 17:11.900
-Walking a dog...
-SHANICE: I have.

17:11.943 --> 17:14.859
My roommate

17:14.903 --> 17:16.339
was turned

17:16.383 --> 17:17.688
by a vampire.

17:17.732 --> 17:19.647
And became a vampire.

17:19.690 --> 17:22.084
She died right
in front of my eyes.

17:22.128 --> 17:24.086
But then she came back to life.

17:24.130 --> 17:25.305
What the fuck?!

17:25.348 --> 17:28.308
But she was different, sick...

17:28.351 --> 17:30.701
unnatural.

17:30.745 --> 17:31.963
And eventually she just...

17:32.007 --> 17:33.661
vanished.

17:33.704 --> 17:36.446
Her future was so bright.

17:36.490 --> 17:38.796
She was such a brilliant LARPer.

17:38.840 --> 17:39.928
GUILLERMO:
I think Shanice and I

17:39.971 --> 17:42.061
might have a mutual friend.

17:45.194 --> 17:47.240
Small world.

17:48.241 --> 17:49.764
This is the life.

17:49.807 --> 17:52.593
Hanging out with
my three favorite gerbils.

17:52.636 --> 17:55.291
I only have one question--
are we inside or outside?

17:55.335 --> 17:57.163
-You need to focus, Sean.
-Huh?

17:57.206 --> 17:59.687
And enjoy the most magical
night of your life.

17:59.730 --> 18:01.036
Hold tight.

18:01.080 --> 18:03.256
What? Whoa...
How are you doing this?!

18:03.299 --> 18:04.822
How are you doing this?!

18:04.866 --> 18:06.259
What's going on now?!

18:06.302 --> 18:07.521
Oh, God, no! Mother Mary!

18:07.564 --> 18:09.262
-Wait for us.
-Here we come.

18:09.305 --> 18:11.307
Hey!

18:13.570 --> 18:16.182
Oh, no, no! Fuck me!

18:16.225 --> 18:18.184
LASZLO:
Now that you've experienced

18:18.227 --> 18:19.924
the pleasure of flying,

18:19.968 --> 18:23.363
enjoy the marvel
of transfiguration.

18:23.406 --> 18:24.146
What?

18:24.190 --> 18:25.843
Bat!

18:25.887 --> 18:27.802
Whoa! Where'd that asshole go?!

18:27.845 --> 18:29.412
Oh, God! Get off!

18:29.456 --> 18:32.067
Look at that,
he's having a lovely time.

18:34.113 --> 18:35.505
-He loves this.
-No, get out of my hair!

18:35.549 --> 18:36.941
Get out of my hair! Get...!

18:36.985 --> 18:38.726
-Sean, look at me.
-No!

18:38.769 --> 18:40.380
Stop that! What are you doing?

18:40.423 --> 18:41.642
It ain't natural!

18:41.685 --> 18:43.557
Are you enjoying
watching me, Sean?

18:43.600 --> 18:45.298
No! Stop it! Get down here!

18:47.474 --> 18:49.215
Ooh, get a good look at this!
Wow!

18:49.258 --> 18:51.652
-Holy shit!
-Sorry, Laszlo.

18:51.695 --> 18:53.219
But, you know,
it's his last night.

18:53.262 --> 18:54.307
LASZLO:
I don't care.

18:54.350 --> 18:56.657
And now for the grand finale.

18:56.700 --> 18:59.399
NANDOR:
We vampires have
dominion of animals.

18:59.442 --> 19:01.792
So we decided
to throw you a little

19:01.836 --> 19:03.054
puppy party.

19:05.274 --> 19:06.623
What have you done?!

19:06.667 --> 19:08.190
-Oh, God!

19:13.456 --> 19:15.415
-Sean.

19:15.458 --> 19:18.896
We did something
really good tonight.

19:18.940 --> 19:21.334
I'm proud of us.

19:21.377 --> 19:22.335
-Yes.
-My boys.

19:29.516 --> 19:31.474
I haven't really had
many real friends.

19:31.518 --> 19:35.348
So, when I met Jenna,
my whole life changed, really.

19:35.391 --> 19:37.480
But she was taken from me.

19:37.524 --> 19:39.482
GUILLERMO:
I guess I never really
think about

19:39.526 --> 19:42.485
the victims or their families.

19:42.529 --> 19:45.488
Uh, I guess I switched
that part of my brain off

19:45.532 --> 19:48.491
with, um, feelings and emotions.

19:48.535 --> 19:50.580
Killing vampires,
killing humans,

19:50.624 --> 19:54.105
collecting victims--
it's all so nasty and ugly.

19:54.149 --> 19:56.412
And, you know, I devoted
my life to it, so...

19:59.154 --> 20:00.851
SHANICE:
So that's why I'm here!

20:00.895 --> 20:04.594
Because vampires cause
nothing but pain!

20:04.638 --> 20:06.466
-Hear, hear.
-Hear, hear.

20:06.509 --> 20:08.032
Come on, say "aye"
if you're with me.

20:08.076 --> 20:10.426
-Aye!
-I have to go.

20:10.470 --> 20:12.298
I'm so sorry.

20:12.341 --> 20:14.822
-I think I left
my toilet running.
-You sure?

20:14.865 --> 20:17.172
-Yeah.
-We're just about to start
crossbow practice.

20:17.216 --> 20:20.393
-What's that?
-Derek got us some mannequins
to use as targets.

20:20.436 --> 20:21.742
Yeah.

20:21.785 --> 20:23.744
-Get a load of this, huh?
-That's a weapon.

20:23.787 --> 20:26.486
-Yeah.
-And those are vampires?

20:26.529 --> 20:28.183
Yeah, I got the costumes
at a Halloween store.

20:28.227 --> 20:30.577
Okay, I don't think
I'd be really...

20:35.364 --> 20:36.626
Damn, pimp!

20:36.670 --> 20:37.932
-I have to go.
-Whoa!

20:37.975 --> 20:39.499
I'm sorry, is-is it just me,

20:39.542 --> 20:40.543
or is this guy an epic pimp?

20:40.587 --> 20:41.631
We'll see you
on Wednesday, right?

20:41.675 --> 20:42.893
No, yeah, a-and if you don't,

20:42.937 --> 20:44.547
it was really nice meeting you.

20:44.591 --> 20:46.897
And, Shanice, I'm very
sorry about your friend.

20:46.941 --> 20:48.986
And you guys should be
really careful

20:49.030 --> 20:50.988
when dealing with vampires--
they're no joke.

20:51.032 --> 20:53.513
CLAUDE:
Hey, hope to see you
again soon, son.

20:53.556 --> 20:55.166
And not just 'cause you,

20:55.210 --> 20:56.646
you have wicked skills
with the C-bow.

20:56.690 --> 20:59.170
You're a mighty cool dude,
Guillermo.

21:00.389 --> 21:02.565
Thank you.

21:05.176 --> 21:06.482
CLAUDE:
Just slide it.

21:06.526 --> 21:08.484
-Yeah, push it to the left...
-Yeah, you got

21:08.528 --> 21:10.573
-to throw your weight into it.
-There you go, you got it.

21:10.617 --> 21:12.358
All right, we'll close it--
don't worry about it.

21:12.401 --> 21:13.881
GUILLERMO:
All right.

21:13.924 --> 21:15.883
Well, that was a lot of fun,
old chap.

21:15.926 --> 21:18.712
I bet you could die a happy man.

21:20.583 --> 21:21.671
He's worse than before.

21:21.715 --> 21:23.412
We've ruined him again.

21:23.456 --> 21:25.022
All the more reason to put him
out of his misery.

21:25.066 --> 21:26.110
Go ahead, Nandor.

21:26.154 --> 21:27.111
Yes.

21:27.155 --> 21:29.288
Here I go.

21:30.201 --> 21:32.552
Head rub time.

21:32.595 --> 21:33.901
LASZLO:
Forgive us, old chap.

21:33.944 --> 21:35.729
Oh, my God.

21:35.772 --> 21:37.426
Who is that piece of ass?

21:37.470 --> 21:39.602
Mamaloosha!

21:39.646 --> 21:40.734
That is Charmaine.

21:40.777 --> 21:42.126
You know her?

21:42.170 --> 21:43.345
She's your wife.

21:43.389 --> 21:45.129
Yeah.

21:45.173 --> 21:47.784
-I wish.
-Seanie!

21:47.828 --> 21:49.569
I've been calling for you
for, like, 20 minutes.

21:49.612 --> 21:51.353
The garbage disposal's
all messed up again.

21:51.397 --> 21:54.400
You are the most
beautiful creature

21:54.443 --> 21:56.227
I have ever seen.

21:56.271 --> 21:57.403
CHARMAINE:
Stop messing around.

21:57.446 --> 21:58.447
SEAN:
I want to spend the rest

21:58.491 --> 22:00.188
of my life making you happy.

22:00.231 --> 22:01.189
This is for you.

22:01.232 --> 22:04.061
It's a token of my undying love.

22:04.105 --> 22:05.846
You emptied out a junk drawer?

22:05.889 --> 22:07.848
-What the hell is
wrong with you?

22:07.891 --> 22:10.633
Wha... what is this?

22:10.677 --> 22:12.026
-What?
-This is beautiful.

22:12.069 --> 22:13.854
Seanie, did you get this for me?

22:13.897 --> 22:15.943
-That is my necklace.
-Oh, my God, Seanie.

22:15.986 --> 22:18.249
-This is a bloody...
-Whoa, whoa, whoa.

22:18.293 --> 22:19.773
Leave them to it, my darling.

22:21.992 --> 22:24.647
I suppose it is quite sweet.

22:24.691 --> 22:26.388
I'll just get it when they die.

22:28.347 --> 22:29.478
NANDOR:
So, we didn't need

22:29.522 --> 22:31.654
to kill Sean after all.

22:31.698 --> 22:35.223
Yes, his mind has been wiped
to a blank slate and now

22:35.266 --> 22:37.965
he can start a new one just
focused on the amazingness

22:38.008 --> 22:39.880
of his wife
and his marriage, and

22:39.923 --> 22:42.448
he doesn't remember
we're vampires at all.

22:42.491 --> 22:44.624
Come on, Colin Robinson.

22:44.667 --> 22:45.973
-We're off.
-Hold on a minute.

22:46.016 --> 22:47.757
I-I may have overdone it.

22:47.801 --> 22:50.499
This one just pissed himself.

22:50.543 --> 22:52.414
Who cares? Come on, let's go.

22:52.458 --> 22:53.807
NANDOR:
So, all in all, I would say

22:53.850 --> 22:55.591
our first Superb Owl celebration

22:55.635 --> 22:58.507
was a marked success.

22:58.551 --> 23:00.857
Even though the owl
didn't show up.

23:00.901 --> 23:02.337
♪ Ooh, night owl♪

23:02.381 --> 23:04.513
♪ Well, yeah♪

23:04.557 --> 23:07.647
-♪ Here come the night owl♪
-♪ Ooh, night owl♪

23:07.690 --> 23:09.866
♪ Oh, oh, oh...♪

23:09.910 --> 23:12.608
Can you tell me,
how is it you haven't aged

23:12.652 --> 23:14.523
after all these years?

23:14.567 --> 23:18.440
I have the gift of eternal life.

23:18.484 --> 23:20.529
Oh, wow.

23:20.573 --> 23:22.488
-Yeah, well.
-Oh, can you

23:22.531 --> 23:24.098
share this gift with me?

23:24.141 --> 23:25.708
I would love to be young again.

23:25.752 --> 23:27.884
Yeah, that's not really
how it works.

23:27.928 --> 23:30.887
If I turned you,
you would stay forever...

23:30.931 --> 23:33.063
like this.

23:33.107 --> 23:34.630
Oh.

23:34.674 --> 23:37.503
-Well, I'll pass, then.
-Yeah.

23:37.546 --> 23:40.897
♪ Ooh, night owl♪

23:43.073 --> 23:46.686
-♪ Now you try to tell me♪
-♪ Ooh, night owl♪

23:46.729 --> 23:48.688
♪ What a fool you've been♪

23:48.731 --> 23:52.692
♪ Ooh, night owl♪

23:52.735 --> 23:57.697
-♪ Yes, but it's all-all over♪
-♪ Ooh, night owl♪

23:57.740 --> 24:00.482
♪ Be on your merry way♪

24:00.526 --> 24:02.136
